env PAGER=cat man timing_property_clock_used_as_data_unconstrained _clock_source_paths
Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_proper...k_source_paths(25.10)    timing_proper...k_source_paths(25.10)

Name
       timing_property_clock_used_as_data_unconstrained_clock_source_paths

Syntax
       timing_property_clock_used_as_data_unconstrained_clock_source_paths

       {true | false}

       Default: true

       Returns a value of true for is_clock_used_as_data timing property  (set
       using the get_property command).

       When  set  to true, the is_clock_used_as_data timing property returns a
       value of true (irrespective of whether the clock source  path  is  con-
       strained  or  unconstrained),  if the pin lies in the clock source path
       and at least one of the clocks arriving at the pin is used as  data  in
       the downstream network of the pin.

       When  set to false, the pins lying in the constrained clock source data
       paths are reported as true. For example, if there is a path from  clock
       source  to  output  port and the output port is unconstrained, then the
       is_clock_used_as_data property will not return true.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

